#: templates/admin/tabs.php:94
msgid "We enter a second loop that permanently deletes each ID that WordPress gave us"
msgstr ""

#: templates/admin/tabs.php:95
msgid "When that first 100 records are no more we ask for the next 100, rinse and repeat, rinse and repeat, ..."
msgstr ""

#: templates/admin/tabs.php:96
msgid "Once we've nuked every record for the selected datasets we can finally show the success screen notice <strong>:)</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: templates/admin/tabs.php:98
msgid "Where things can go wrong during this process is:"
msgstr ""

#: templates/admin/tabs.php:100
msgid "We hit the 30 second server timeout configured on some hosting server's that kills the active process (ours), or"
msgstr ""

#: templates/admin/tabs.php:101
msgid "WordPress maxes out its memory allocation looping through each batch of 100 ID's"
msgstr ""

#: templates/admin/tabs.php:103
msgid "Re-opening Store Toolkit from the WordPress Administration and hitting continue will resolve most issues. Happy nuking! <strong>:)</strong>"
msgstr ""

